This paper focuses on the process of developers locating and fixing performance bugs, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). The study involves developers working with a profiling and analysis tool, which suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the use of visualization and sketches to aid in understanding and communication, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer graphics (cs.CY).
